<Link id="l00388" /><CodeLine lineNumber="388"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Iterator that reports all the invoke state changes in a range of machine</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00389" /><CodeLine lineNumber="389"><Highlight kind="comment">/// basic blocks.  Changes to the null state are reported whenever a call that</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00390" /><CodeLine lineNumber="390"><Highlight kind="comment">/// may unwind to caller is encountered.  The MBB range is expected to be an</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00391" /><CodeLine lineNumber="391"><Highlight kind="comment">/// entire function or funclet, and the start and end of the range are treated</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00392" /><CodeLine lineNumber="392"><Highlight kind="comment">/// as being in the NullState even if there&#39;s not an unwind-to-caller call</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00393" /><CodeLine lineNumber="393"><Highlight kind="comment">/// before the first invoke or after the last one (i.e., the first state change</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00394" /><CodeLine lineNumber="394"><Highlight kind="comment">/// reported is the first change to something other than NullState, and a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00395" /><CodeLine lineNumber="395"><Highlight kind="comment">/// change back to NullState is always reported at the end of iteration).</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00531" /><CodeLine lineNumber="531"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Emit the language-specific data that &#95;&#95;C&#95;specific&#95;handler expects.  This</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00532" /><CodeLine lineNumber="532"><Highlight kind="comment">/// handler lives in the x64 Microsoft C runtime and allows catching or cleaning</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00533" /><CodeLine lineNumber="533"><Highlight kind="comment">/// up after faults with &#95;&#95;try, &#95;&#95;except, and &#95;&#95;finally.  The typeinfo values</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00534" /><CodeLine lineNumber="534"><Highlight kind="comment">/// are not really RTTI data, but pointers to filter functions that return an</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00535" /><CodeLine lineNumber="535"><Highlight kind="comment">/// integer (1, 0, or -1) indicating how to handle the exception. For &#95;&#95;finally</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00536" /><CodeLine lineNumber="536"><Highlight kind="comment">/// blocks and other cleanups, the landing pad label is zero, and the filter</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00537" /><CodeLine lineNumber="537"><Highlight kind="comment">/// function is actually a cleanup handler with the same prototype.  A catch-all</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00538" /><CodeLine lineNumber="538"><Highlight kind="comment">/// entry is modeled with a null filter function field and a non-zero landing</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00539" /><CodeLine lineNumber="539"><Highlight kind="comment">/// pad label.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00540" /><CodeLine lineNumber="540"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00541" /><CodeLine lineNumber="541"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Possible filter function return values:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00542" /><CodeLine lineNumber="542"><Highlight kind="comment">///   EXCEPTION&#95;EXECUTE&#95;HANDLER (1):</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00543" /><CodeLine lineNumber="543"><Highlight kind="comment">///     Jump to the landing pad label after cleanups.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00544" /><CodeLine lineNumber="544"><Highlight kind="comment">///   EXCEPTION&#95;CONTINUE&#95;SEARCH (0):</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00545" /><CodeLine lineNumber="545"><Highlight kind="comment">///     Continue searching this table or continue unwinding.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00546" /><CodeLine lineNumber="546"><Highlight kind="comment">///   EXCEPTION&#95;CONTINUE&#95;EXECUTION (-1):</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00547" /><CodeLine lineNumber="547"><Highlight kind="comment">///     Resume execution at the trapping PC.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00548" /><CodeLine lineNumber="548"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00549" /><CodeLine lineNumber="549"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Inferred table structure:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00550" /><CodeLine lineNumber="550"><Highlight kind="comment">///   struct Table &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00551" /><CodeLine lineNumber="551"><Highlight kind="comment">///     int NumEntries;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00552" /><CodeLine lineNumber="552"><Highlight kind="comment">///     struct Entry &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00553" /><CodeLine lineNumber="553"><Highlight kind="comment">///       imagerel32 LabelStart;       // Inclusive</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00554" /><CodeLine lineNumber="554"><Highlight kind="comment">///       imagerel32 LabelEnd;         // Exclusive</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00555" /><CodeLine lineNumber="555"><Highlight kind="comment">///       imagerel32 FilterOrFinally;  // One means catch-all.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00556" /><CodeLine lineNumber="556"><Highlight kind="comment">///       imagerel32 LabelLPad;        // Zero means &#95;&#95;finally.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00557" /><CodeLine lineNumber="557"><Highlight kind="comment">///     &#125; Entries&#91;NumEntries&#93;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00558" /><CodeLine lineNumber="558"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#125;;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00559" /><CodeLine lineNumber="559"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">void</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> WinException::emitCSpecificHandlerTable(</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machinefunction">MachineFunction</a> &#42;MF) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
